HEADWORD: Blancmange
<hw>Blanc*mange"</hw> <pr>(bl⟦aum⟧*m⟦aum⟧Nzh; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>blancmanger</ets>, lit. white food; <ets>blanc</ets> white
+ <ets>manger</ets> to eat.]</ety> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A
preparation for desserts, etc., made from isinglass, sea moss,
cornstarch, or other gelatinous or starchy substance, with milk, usually
sweetened and flavored, and shaped in a mold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

